pQAIM21Yw4eNdbha2Rxkcg
I don't give 5 stars very often.   Let me just start by saying that this dining adventure takes a while. Our reservation was at 715 and we left at 930. There are multiple courses and cooking times for your food. (The proteins are all delivered raw and you cook them yourself in the fondue pot.)  As long as your are comfortable with the fact that it is expensive, it takes a while to have the full experience, and that it is interactive (requires you to do your own cooking in the proteins) then you really should not have anything to complain about. As long as you know what you're in for, you'll have an amazing time.  As far as the quality of the food, the staff, the atmosphere and the flavors, I can only say one thing: DYNAMITE.   I have had more expensive meals in my life. Price does not dictate the quality of a meal. Everything adds up to be the best date night, special occasion, etc that my money can buy. Any time I want a special dining experience The Melting Pot is #1, #2, #3 on my list every single time. I just can't say enough positive things about it. If you think it's too good to be true, go find out for yourself. It's not and you'll thank me later.

